EUROPA

(Met. rr, 8334375)

[Jupiter having fallen in love with Europa, daughter of Agenor, king oi Phoenicia, decided to win her by strategy. Calling¹ Mercury, his trusty messenger, he ordered him to go to Phoenicia and drive the king's herd of cattle down towards the seashore. Mercury obeyed, and soon the cattle were grazing in a meadow near the ocean, where the princess and her companions were play- ing. Then the father and ruler oi the gods took upon himself the form of a snow-white bull, and joined the royal herd. Europa noticed him, and seeing that he was gentle, approached.
